<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Liana of unknown height, apparently glabrous in all parts; stems glabrous. Leaves petiolate, 5.5-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-8 cm, 3-5-lobed to near the base, the 4th and 5th lobes often only partially developed, lobes oblong-elliptic or lanceolate, 0.5-2.5 cm wide, acuminate; base truncate, abaxially paler; petioles 4-6 cm. Inflorescence of compounded axillary cymes 20-30 cm long; peduncles 9-12 cm long; 2-6th degree peduncles 1-4 cm; bracteoles 1 mm, oblong, scale-like, caduous; pedicels 7-11 mm; sepals subequal, 5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, elliptic, coriaceous, convex, outer rounded, minutely mucronate, inner 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
scarious, rounded; corolla c. 4 cm long, pink, funnel-shaped, glabrous; limb c. 2.5 cm diam., the midpetaline bands ending in teeth. Capsules 6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, ovoid with a slender persistent style, glabrous; seeds (possibly immature) 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 mm, pilose with long white hairs on the margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
