<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species has been identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is clearly related to that very variable species. However, it is immediately distinguished by the compound axillary inflorescences which reach 30 cm in length and are divided up to six times. Additionally, the sepals, corolla and capsules are all much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
